<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Document</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/course.css">
    <style>
        @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Poppins:ital,wght@0,300;0,400;0,500;0,600;1,200;1,300;1,400;1,500&family=Smooch&display=swap');
    </style>
</head>

<body>
    <div class="parent">
        <div class="child">
            <h1>
                <%= course_title %>
            </h1>
        </div>
        <div class="child">
            <img src="https://www.courseduck.com/global/images/abdul_bari.jpg" alt="" class="imgg">
            <h5>Taught by: <%= teacher_name %>
            </h5>
        </div>
    </div>
    <hr style="text-align:left;margin-left:0">

    <div class="sect">
        <!-- <h3><%= course_description %></h3> -->
        <h3>Course Description</h3>
        <p>Data structures and algorithms (DSA) goes through solutions to standard problems in detail and gives you an
            insight into how efficient it is to use each one of them. It also teaches you the science of evaluating the
            efficiency of an algorithm. This enables you to choose the best of various choices.</p>
    </div>
    <br>

    <div class="sect">
        <h3>Assignments</h3>
        <p>All assignments uploaded by your instructor can be viewed here</p>
        <table>
            <tr class="heads">
                <td>Name</td>
                <td>Description</td>
                <td>Time</td>
            </tr>
            <% for(var i=0; i < result3.length; i++) { %>
                <tr>
                    <td>
                        <a href="/student-home/assignment/<%=result3[i].assignment_id%>">
                            <%= result3[i].assignment_title %>
                        </a>

                    </td>
                    <td>
                        <%= result3[i].assignment_description %>
                    </td>
                    <td>
                        <%= result3[i].deadline %>
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <% } %>
        </table>
    </div>

</body>

</html>